// HTTP Server Entry Point
// Bootstraps the Bun HTTP server, registers the scratch session, initializes
// shared services, and wires up HTTP routing and WebSocket handling. Also
// registers process signal handlers for graceful shutdown.

On startup, a scratch session is registered at ~/.mermaid-collab/scratch.
Shared stateless services (Validator, Renderer, WebSocketHandler) are
instantiated once and passed into route handlers.
The WebSocket handler manager is initialized for global access by other modules.
Placeholder managers are created at /tmp to satisfy the handleAPI signature;
real per-session managers are created inside handleAPI on each request.

FUNCTION fetch(req, server) -> Response
  CALLS: handleMCPRequest (http-handler), handleKodexAPI (kodex-api), handleOnboardingAPI (onboarding-api), handleAPI (api)
  Parse the request URL.
  IF path is "/ws", upgrade to a collaboration WebSocket; return 500 if upgrade fails.
  IF path starts with "/terminal/", extract sessionId from path and upgrade to a
  terminal WebSocket with { type: "terminal", sessionId } attached; return 500 if fails.
  IF path is "/mcp", forward to handleMCPRequest.
  IF path starts with "/api/kodex", forward to handleKodexAPI.
  IF path starts with "/api/onboarding", forward to handleOnboardingAPI.
  IF path starts with "/api/", forward to handleAPI.
  IF the UI dist directory exists, attempt to serve the file from ui/dist/.
  IF the file exists, return it with the appropriate MIME type.
  IF the path is not a static asset extension, serve index.html as SPA fallback.
  Return 404 if nothing matched.

---

FUNCTION websocket.open(ws)
  CALLS: handleTerminalOpen (websocket), WebSocketHandler.handleConnection (handler)
  IF connection type is "terminal", call handleTerminalOpen.
  ELSE treat as collaboration connection: call wsHandler.handleConnection and
  send a "connected" message with the current connection count.

---

FUNCTION websocket.message(ws, message)
  CALLS: handleTerminalMessage (websocket), WebSocketHandler.handleMessage (handler)
  IF connection type is "terminal", call handleTerminalMessage.
  ELSE forward the string message to wsHandler.handleMessage.

---

FUNCTION websocket.close(ws)
  CALLS: handleTerminalClose (websocket), WebSocketHandler.handleDisconnection (handler)
  IF connection type is "terminal", call handleTerminalClose.
  ELSE call wsHandler.handleDisconnection.

---

FUNCTION websocket.error(ws, error)
  CALLS: handleTerminalError (websocket)
  IF connection type is "terminal", call handleTerminalError.
  Collaboration errors are handled elsewhere.

---

FUNCTION SIGINT handler
  CALLS: ptyManager.killAll (terminal/index)
  Kill all active PTY sessions and exit with code 0.

---

FUNCTION SIGTERM handler
  CALLS: ptyManager.killAll (terminal/index)
  Kill all active PTY sessions and exit with code 0.
